@*
    Standard loading-block — spinner + label, accessible via the
    role="status" / aria-live="polite" pair so a screen reader
    announces the load when it starts.

    Replaces the eight-line inline pattern that was duplicated
    across every Wells / Runs / Detail / Edit page:

        <div class="enki-loading-block" role="status" aria-live="polite">
            <div class="enki-spinner" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div class="enki-loading-text">Fetching surveys from API…</div>
        </div>

    Now:

        <EnkiLoading Label="Fetching surveys from API…" />

    Default label is "Loading…" so a bare <EnkiLoading /> works on
    pages where the more specific copy isn't useful.
*@

<div class="enki-loading-block" role="status" aria-live="polite">
    <div class="enki-spinner" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="enki-loading-text">@Label</div>
</div>

